{
  "doc_id": "38795",
  "text": "Isavuconazole may be the best alternative to posaconazole because of excellent sensitivity (MICs ≤0.007 mcg/ mL) including isolates resistant to fluconazole or voriconazole. [CITATION_1] However, clinical experience of isavuconazole is limited: 3 of 7 patients failed treatment with isavuconazole. [CITATION_2] and in animal models comparing isavuconazole with other azoles have not been reported. Despite these limitations, isavuconazole should be an effective alternative to posaconazole.",
